The paper deals with the problem of learning the optimal action-value function in Markov decision processes (MDPs) using reinforcement learning (RL) algorithms. This falls under the broad area of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of data structures (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY) to model and solve the MDPs. Additionally, the paper discusses the sample complexity of RL algorithms, which is a topic in mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
